{
  "stem": "1895.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, the signs of life returned to the building, as I remembered it as a child.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my mother told me to wash up.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She prepared some food for me, and she told me to lie down and go to sleep, because she knew I had worked all night, and I needed the rest.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I want to [SIGHS] describe my experiences by reading this part of my memoirs now.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 22 SECONDS] My mother made me go to bed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "She told me I had to rest after this terrible ordeal, and get ready for work again.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I went to bed, but sleep eluded me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I hadn't told my parents of what I saw in the field that day, but I couldn't stop thinking about it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I remember thinking, in my adolescent innocence, that if I could just talk to Hitler, and explain how terribly people were suffering because of his policies, he would listen and bring a stop to it.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I could not imagine that an enlightened, cultured, and educated people could make the cold-blooded murder of men, women, and children state policy.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I was also kept awake by visions of my dear friends, whom I cherished.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Eventually, I got out of bed, and I saw my mother packing some of my things into a bag. 'Mother, what are you doing?' I asked. 'This is for you to take along to work in case they don't let you return to the ghetto.'",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I grabbed her hands and I said, 'No, wait, mama.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm not going back to work.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whatever happens, we should stay together.' 'Don't be ridiculous.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You have to go.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
